# Super Alpha workflow

This is a live MetaAPI / MT5 auto-trading system. Correctness beats speed.

## Mandatory order

1. **Cases → variables → risks → cost → then code** (never reverse).
2. Do not blindly add global sub-second polling for all accounts.
3. Prefer broker-side TP/SL (execution) + control-plane for open baskets only.

## Before coding

State briefly:
- Goal (one)
- Cases / edge cases
- Variables involved
- Risks (esp. live positions, force-close, naked TP/SL)
- Cost impact (MetaAPI hosting / API)
- Acceptance checks (commands or live checks)

## After coding (QA — required)

Run what applies:
- Targeted verify scripts under `scripts/_verify-*.ts` when touching protect/DCA/engine
- Lint diagnostics on edited TS/TSX
- Do not claim done if open baskets can be naked or force-closed incorrectly

## Live account safety

- Never force-close baskets on API lag / partial orphan alone.
- Do not change logic mid-open-basket unless explicitly requested.
- yjgoja / production logins: keep lots small unless asked.

## Scope

One job per request. If the user asks for “everything”, split into ordered steps and finish the first with QA before expanding.
